# 5. docker rmi

Purpose:

Removes a Docker image.

Command:

```bash
docker rmi image_name
```

Example:

```bash
docker rmi ubuntu
```

or

```bash
docker rmi ubuntu:latest
```

If an image is currently being used by a container:

Docker shows:

```text
conflict

unable to delete image

container is using its referenced image
```

Solution:

Delete the container first.

Then delete the image.

---

# 6. docker tag

Purpose:

Assign another name or version tag to an existing image.

It does NOT create a new image.

Syntax:

```bash
docker tag existing_image new_image
```

Example:

```bash
docker tag pushpa-ubuntu:v1 pushpa-ubuntu:latest
```

Now:

```bash
docker images
```

shows:

```text
pushpa-ubuntu   v1

pushpa-ubuntu   latest
```

Both tags point to the same Image ID.

---

# Important

docker tag does not duplicate the image.

It only creates another reference to the same image.

